org.kiji.schema
Class KijiDataWriter

java.lang.Object
  org.kiji.schema.KijiDataWriter
All Implemented Interfaces:
Closeable
Direct Known Subclasses:
WrappedDataWriter
public abstract class KijiDataWriter
extends Object
implements Closeable

Base class for writers of Kiji data to different output sinks.

A data writer must be configured with the name of a Kiji column family writes will target. A data writer may optionally be configured with the name of a Kiji column qualifier writes will target. If the writer has not been configured with a Kiji column qualifier, all writes must specify the Kiji column qualifier.

A KijiDataWriter may buffer writes before output. Clients should use the flush() method to force the data writer to output its buffered writes. Closing a data writer using close() will flush all writes and release any resources used by the data writer.

write

protected abstract void write(EntityId id,
                              String family,
                              String qualifier,
                              org.apache.avro.Schema schema,
                              long timestamp,
                              Object value)
                       throws IOException,
                              InterruptedException
Writes a value at the current timestamp and reports progress.

All other write methods of Kiji data writers delegate to this method. Subclasses should override this method to implement desired write functionality.

Parameters:
id - The entity id of the row to write to.
family - The family to write to.
qualifier - The key (column qualifier) to write the data to.
schema - The writer schema for the value.
timestamp - The timestamp at which the data will be written.
value - The data payload.
Throws:
IOException - If there is a problem writing.
InterruptedException - If the thread is interrupted while writing.
